{
  "texts": [
    "The participants were randomly presented with two passages in one session, so a participant could have encountered two human-written passages.",
    "We cannot confirm if this approach may have skewed the results, and we thus regard it as a limitation of this study.",
    "Furthermore, since the ratio of human-to AI-written passages was two to one (2:1), the study relies on descriptive analysis comparison of accuracy ratio and hence the measures of sensitivity and specificity are reported.",
    "While many demographic data were collected, we did not determine if English was participants' native language, which might be important because fluency could be an essential factor in deciphering authorship.",
    "Regardless, the next version of the tool should include native languages as an important criterion."
  ]
}